Some people make the question of aspect depend on the nature of the soil, letting vines planted in dry situations face east and north and those in a damp one south. Moreover, they borrow rules from the vines themselves, by plant— ing early varieties in cold situations, so that their ripening may come before the cold weather‚ and fruit- trees and vines that dislike dew, with an eastern aspect, so that the sun may carry off the moisture at once, but those that like dew, facing west or even north, so that they may enjoy it for a longer time. But the rest, virtually following Nature 5 sy stem, have recom- mended that vines and trees should be placed so as to face north- east; and Democritus is of opinion that the fruit so grown also has more scent.
